Liquid Telecom South Africa has announced that CEO Kyle Whitehill is leaving the company at the end of his contract. “Kyle has decided to return home to be with his family who remained in the UK during his time in South Africa,” said Nic Rudnick, Group CEO at Liquid Telecom. “We thank Kyle for his determination and drive that has seen the company go through many positive changes and renewed focus. With our strong leadership team in place, the company will continue to build Africa’s digital future.” Whitehill will depart the company on 20 March 2018.